I am creating a hamburger menu with multiple levels. 
here is a jsfiddle with the basic code: https://jsfiddle.net/TheBB23/hnsjym9u/
Some things work ok, others need improvement. 
I am new to javascript and jquery that&#39;s why I guess most problems occur there. 
I will list here problems that I am facing and I would appreciate you helping me with. 
1. Clicking the + (expand button) should not close the menu the menu should still close and reset to closed state, when clicking a link in it. 
2. Clicking the minus should hide the submenu but not close the menu
3. Clicking the + should only expand the corresponding submenu, right now it opens all menus. 
4. Not as important: is there a way to have the links displayed as block (fill the whole width) and have the buttons in the same line (My only idea is to move them with CSS by the amount of pixels I want them but that&#39;s not the best solution I guess)

Please note that the menu should run on a backend that does not allow me to specify each link differently. 

